ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: HUNTINGTON BEACH; 
CORONERS IDENTIFY BODY AS THAT OF MISSING MAN 
The coroner's office has confirmed that a body that washed ashore in Huntington 
Beach about 5 p.m. Sunday is that of Craig Hand, 20, a brain tumor patient who 
disappeared Thursday in the surf at Bolsa Chica State Beach, police said. 
The body was found lying between the Huntington Beach Pier and lifeguard tower 
No. 3. 
Hand, who suffered from debilitating seizures, was last seen by his girlfriend 
at 2 p.m. Thursday entering the water off 11th Street. A search began 20 
minutes later. 
